7:
Hah-hah-hah! You monsters have
underestimated me!
8:
My Lord's Aegis is impenetrable!
Acknowledge your mistake in
challenging me and end this
reckless attack at once!
12: I think your knees are shaking...
17:
W-wait! Take another step forward,
and you'll be exposing yourself to
danger!
21:
Well, we won't exactly be able to
attack if we stay back here...
24: Maybe you can just follow along.
28:
H-how do you expect me to do that
when my knees are trembling with
the force of a thousand
earthquakes?!
33:
No matter how great the shield, it
cannot strike at foes beyond the
wielder's reach.
35:
Too often, I find myself quaking in
my greaves while my allies charge
full speed ahead, widening the
distance between us!
36:
But then epiphany struck—there
may be a way for me to remain in
the front lines beside my allies
without moving my legs! The
solution would be...
56:
Why surfing though? Wait, do you
mean to use your shield as a
surfboard?
60:
My Lord's Aegis automatically grants
absolute defense! Imagine what
would happen if I were to ride the
shield!
63:
I'd gain the mobility to protect you
anywhere you are! It couldn't be
more perfect!
73:
But that's... Well, I guess it's worth
trying...
78:
Exactly! We won't know until we try!
Now, Lord's Aegis—off we go to the
horizon and beyond!
83:
Urk, no! Why do you refuse me,
Lord's Aegis?!
86:
Think it might have something to do
with your shaking knees?
92:
If you have trouble riding the shield,
how about affixing yourself to it?
96:
By that you mean affixing the shield
to Razelt's legs?
99:
Yes. That way, Razelt won't be
knocked off.
102:
Hm... I know it's only a replica, but
modifying it might be—
108: I don't mind in the least!
111: Oh, so you're okay with it...
115:
As prince and fourteenth in line to
the throne, I'll allow it!
118:
I appreciate you coming up with the
idea! Do with the Lord's Aegis
whatever you deem necessary!
122:
Okay, we'll try to get it done without
hurting you.
126:
Figuring out how to attach it to
Razelt's legs comes first.
132:
There, that should do it for the leg
fasteners.
136:
We made sure nothing else is
affected. All that's left is to surf.
141:
V-very well. Prepare to shower me
with praise and applause.
154:
You're all hunched over, but... at
least you're standing! Now try
moving forward, Razelt!
162:
Bwahahahaha! Now, Lord's
Aegis—off we go to the horizon and
beyond!
168:
Bwahahaha! You may as well call
me the Prince of the Open Seas now!
194:
Don't just stand there! Help me
already!
198:
That's quite the speed you're going
on the water... Any chance you can
remove the fasteners on your legs
and try to swim back to shore?
201:
What a foolish thing to ask of
someone who's never taken a single
swimming lesson in their life! *glug
glug*
207:
What a shame. I wonder what
exactly went wrong.
212:
Hm, I can think of at least a few
things...
